{:tx/id #hlc "1774542275/0/af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/agent "af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-PERF-003: Binary cache invalidation on every transaction — CLI-mode performance regression. PROBLEM: Every write_tx() call marks the binary cache (store.bin) as stale. Cache rebuilt on next load_store(). For daemon mode this is fine (store in memory). For CLI mode (no daemon), every command writing a transaction triggers full cache rebuild on next read command. Session 032 documented: '30s braid status caused by RFL-2 txn per command invalidating all caches.' The daemon (Session 032 solution) amortizes this. JUSTIFICATION: The daemon architecture (ADR-STORE-006 revised) solves this for the primary use case. But CLI-mode fallback (when daemon isn't running) remains O(n) per read-after-write. This matters for CI pipelines and automated testing where the daemon may not be running. Incremental cache updates (append new datoms to binary cache rather than full invalidation) would make CLI-mode viable for larger stores. SOLUTION: Add incremental binary cache updates: serialize new datoms as a delta appended to store.bin. On load, read base + deltas. Compact periodically. VERIFICATION: CLI-mode 'braid status' after 'braid observe' takes <2s for 200K-datom store. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Complements F-PERF-001 (merge performance). FILES: crates/braid/src/layout.rs (write_tx), live_store.rs. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 4. EFFORT: 8h."
